  "title": "Accountant (Construction)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Overview:</strong></p><ul><li>Handles full duties of accounts including GST submissions, month-end closing reports, financial reports and ensure all intercompany balances, transactions and reconciliations are properly reconciled</li><li>Management of cash flow and assist in preparation of cash flow projection, project costing and WIP accounting</li><li>Prepare and ensure monthly management report, are in accordance to FRS and accounting policies</li><li>Prepare and implement financial and accounting policies and procedures for the company and make recommendations for improvements</li><li>Liaise with external auditors, tax agents and other professional advisors for statutory compliances</li><li>Assist in the management and maintenance of robust internal control processes</li><li>Act as the key support and backup to the Head of Accounts</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accounting/Finance/ACCA or equivalent, CPA and CA preferred</li><li>Working experience in construction industry with at least 10 years in handling full duties of accounts</li><li>Meticulous, detailed oriented and able to multi-task</li><li>Able to lead, train and supervise a team of accounting staff</li><li>Proficient in Sage 300 ACCPAC accounting software and Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Five-and-half-day work week. (Alternate Saturdays)</li><li>Working location: North</li></ul><p>Please include the following information in your resume.</p><ul><li>Current & Expected Salary</li><li>Reason(s) for leaving</li><li>Notice Period / Availability to commence work</li></ul><p>By submitting any application or resume to us, you will be deemed to have agreed and consented to us disclosing your personal information to prospective employers for their consideration.</p><p>We regret only short-listed candidates will be notified.<br />EA License | 18C9251 WGT Group<br />Registration No | R22111484</p>",
